### 1. Simple GET Request
# The most basic HTTP request - fetch data from an API
GET https://httpbin.org/get
Accept: application/json

### 2. GET with Query Parameters
# URLs with query parameters work seamlessly
GET https://httpbin.org/get?name=nrest&version=0.1.3
User-Agent: nrest.nvim/0.1.3

### 3. GET with Custom Headers
# Add any headers you need
GET https://httpbin.org/headers
Accept: application/json
X-Custom-Header: nrest-demo
X-Request-ID: 12345

### 4. POST with JSON Body
# Send JSON data to an API
POST https://httpbin.org/post
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
  "message": "Hello from nrest.nvim!",
  "plugin": "nrest.nvim",
  "version": "0.1.3",
  "features": ["fast", "lightweight", "zero dependencies"]
}

### 5. PUT Request
# Update resources with PUT
PUT https://httpbin.org/put
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 123,
  "status": "updated",
  "timestamp": "2025-10-19"
}

### 6. PATCH Request
# Partial updates with PATCH
PATCH https://httpbin.org/patch
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "active"
}

### 7. DELETE Request
# Remove resources
DELETE https://httpbin.org/delete
Authorization: Bearer demo-token

### 8. Request with Bearer Token Authentication
# See auth-examples.http for more auth methods
GET https://httpbin.org/bearer
Authorization: Bearer demo-token-12345

### 9. Response Format Demo
# This endpoint returns JSON - nrest.nvim will format it with jq
GET https://httpbin.org/json
Accept: application/json

### 10. Check Your IP
# See what IP address the server sees
GET https://httpbin.org/ip

### 11. User Agent Echo
# The server echoes back your user agent
GET https://httpbin.org/user-agent
User-Agent: nrest.nvim-demo/0.1.3

### 12. Delay Response (Timeout Test)
# This request waits 2 seconds before responding
# Good for testing async behavior
GET https://httpbin.org/delay/2

### 13. Status Code Testing
# Test different HTTP status codes
GET https://httpbin.org/status/200

### 14. Random Data
# Get random UUID
GET https://httpbin.org/uuid

